This paper belongs to the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it involves the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze social media data. It also falls under the sub-category of social media (cs.SI) as it focuses on analyzing online conversations about a specific topic. Additionally, the paper touches upon issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and privacy (cs.CY), which are relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper also has elements of social computing (cs.SOC) as it explores how cultural differences impact people's reactions to data privacy breaches.
